  "response": "Getting into Oxford University is highly competitive. Here are some key steps:\n\n1. Academic Excellence\n- Achieve top grades in high school/secondary school\n- Take challenging courses\n- Score exceptionally well on standardized tests\n- Maintain a strong academic record\n\n2. Application Requirements\n- Complete the UCAS application\n- Write a compelling personal statement\n- Obtain strong letters of recommendation\n- Demonstrate intellectual curiosity\n\n3. Subject-Specific Preparation\n- Research the specific course requirements\n- Show deep interest in your chosen subject\n- Participate in related extracurricular activities\n\n4. Admissions Tests\n- Take required subject-specific admissions tests\n- Prepare thoroughly for these exams\n- Practice past papers and mock tests\n\n5. Interview Preparation\n- If shortlisted, prepare for rigorous interviews\n- Practice critical thinking and discussion skills\n- Show passion for your subject\n- Demonstrate ability to think analytically\n\n6. Additional Considerations\n- Learn about Oxford's college system\n- Choose the right college\n- Consider international student requirements\n- Demonstrate leadership and achievements\n\n7. Financial Planning\n- Research scholarship opportunities\n- Understand tuition and living costs\n- Explore funding options\n\nSeek guidance from school counselors and current Oxford students for personalized advice.",
